-- Jeter to Undergo Ankle Surgery With Recovery Time of 4-5 Months
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-10-17T20:13:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-17/jeter-to-undergo-ankle-surgery-with-recovery-time-of-4-5-months.html
New York  Yankees shortstop Derek
Jeter will undergo surgery Oct. 20 on his left ankle and should
make a complete recovery in 4-5 months, the Major League
Baseball team said on its website.  Jeter, the Yankees’ 38-year-old captain, was injured
chasing down a ground ball during the 12th inning of the team’s
6-4 loss to the Detroit Tigers in Game 1 of the American League
Championship Series.  The Tigers lead the best-of-seven series 3-0. Game 4 is
tonight.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  